   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
      <p>
Diagnosis
</p>
      <p>
Representative of the family 
<tp:taxon-name>Dzhulfitidae</tp:taxon-name>
with large conch; maximum adult diameters about 
120 mm
. Adult stage with trapezoidal whorl profile. Subadult stage with conical ventrolateral nodes, adult stage with weak ribs. Suture line with very small external lobe reaching only half the depth of adventive lobe.
</p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
